# Regression: multi-overload dispatch inside an if-arm body must
# propagate branches the same way it does at the top level. `in` has
# both `({K: V} str -- bool)` and `(str str -- bool)` overloads.
# Before this fix `checkIfBlock` walked arm bodies in single-state
# mode, so when `in` populated branchSpawn the alternatives were
# silently dropped and the live state rewound to pre-dispatch — `in`
# effectively became a no-op inside the arm.

def f ({v} --)
    seen!
    true if
        @seen "x" in not if
            "found" wl
        end
    end
end
